---
import Button from "./Button.astro";
---

<section class="feature">
  <picture class="main-image">
    <source
      srcset="assets/images/image-web-3-desktop.jpg"
      media="(min-width: 43.75em)"
    />
    <img
      src="assets/images/image-web-3-mobile.jpg"
      alt="A vibrant and colorful arrangement of various wooden blocks in different shapes and sizes. The blocks are painted in bold hues of red, blue, yellow, and orange, and are placed on a black surface. Some blocks have cut-out shapes, while others have cylindrical pegs inserted into holes, creating a visually engaging and playful composition."
    />
  </picture>
  <h1 class="heading-1">The Bright Future of Web 3.0?</h1>
  <div class="flow" style="--flow-spacer: 1.5rem">
    <p>
      We dive into the next evolution of the web that claims to put the power of
      the platforms back into the hands of the people. But is it really
      fulfilling its promise?
    </p>
    <Button href="#" theme="primary">Read more</Button>
  </div>
</section>

<style lang="scss">
  @use "../styles/abstracts/" as *;

  .feature {
    display: grid;
    gap: $feature-gap-mobile;

    @include mq(medium) {
      grid-column: 1 / 3;
      grid-row: 1 / 3;
      grid-template-columns: subgrid;
      grid-template-rows: subgrid;
      gap: $feature-gap-desktop;
    }

    & h1 {
      order: -1;
      s
    }

    & picture {
      @include mq(medium) {
        grid-column: 1 / 3;
      }
    }

    & div {
      @include mq(medium) {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: start;
        justify-content: space-between;
      }
    }
  }
</style>
